title: Findlay Flyers Summer Training Series
description: This is a summer training series held in Findlay, Ohio.  The series consists of three races over distances of 10-36 kilometers.  Points will be earned for top performances.
course: The course will be on lightly traveled country roads.  Center-line rule will be in effect.
registration: The series is open to anyone.    The cost to compete in the entire series is $20 per person.  Cash and Check payment available onsite.  USAC annual license holders must pay $3 per event for insurance coverage, single-day license holders are covered under the single-day license.  Single-day licenses are available through USAC for $15 per day.
notes:
More information at:
facebook.com/findlaybikeracing
Ben (Race Director) 419-889-2498
Small trophy awarded for points winner.
directions: This series takes place in Hancock County at Riverbend Park and Mt. Blanchard Park.

title: Mayor's TwiLight Ride of Columbus

address.street: BIcentennial Park, 233 South Civic Center Drive

description:
Join Mayor Michael B. Coleman and other home town celebrities for an evening of bicycling through the heart of Columbus on Friday, July 11. Hop on your bike, grab your bike light and helmet and dont miss Columbus finest evening ride. The bike route will be the best tour of Columbus on two wheels! -a unique tour takes riders through the vibrant downtown area, and views of parks, city landmarks, and a wide variety of architecture in scenic neighborhoods.

Stick around afterwards for the *free* Rhythm on the River concert at Bicentennial Park!
course: A 15 mile tour of Columbus with the Mayor of Columbus.

title: The Battle For Danville Road Race

description: Come join us, Saturday August 16rd, 2014 for a fun filled day of cyclocross.  Lady Gnar Shredders is hosting a FREE cyclocross clinic for women of all ages.  This clinic is geared towards the beginner to intermediate rider. (Its okay if you never ridden a cyclocross bike or on the dirt!)  Clinicians hosting will be OVCX overall CX winner 2012, and nationally ranked racer Katie Arnold and Ohio State CX champ, Tori Steen.
registration: Free to all riders. Please visit ladygnarshredder.com for more information

Ride for All People
description: A fun ride and open house to introduce Bikes for All People, a cycling outreach program of Church and Community Development for All People.
course: 10 mile course rides through downtown Columbus to North Bank Park.  20 mile ride continues on the bike trail to Whetstone Park.
registration: No fee.  You can sign up on line to let us know you are coming or you can show up on the day of the ride.
notes: Refreshments after the ride in our new shop.
directions: The ride will start at Bikes for All People, 934 Parsons Ave., Columbus, OH.  Parking in the lot just north of and adjacent to the shop.

title: Columbus Cyclocross Practice Series
description: Columbus' own cyclocross practices. Hone your skills at mounts, dismounts, cornering, starts, stops, diverse conditions, and more! Open to riders of all levels, from "I've never ridden a bike off-road" to "I podium at Cincy3" Organized instruction followed by brief mock racing.
course: Basic short format courses will vary from week to week to highlight and require different skills.
registration: It is free to participate, but you are required to fill out a USAC waiver for each practice. You are strongly encouraged to donate to support the costs involved with cyclocross practices.
directions: Big Run Park, 4201 Clime Rd Columbus, OH 43228, once you have entered the park, follow the signs to the Derby Hill. Parking is available on the paved strips adjacent to the Derby Hill.
